Positron emission tomography in thyroid cancer management. Selected patients with thyroid cancer can benefit from the use of PET imaging with FDG or with I-124. The PET scan impacts on management by providing (1) more accurate information about staging of patients in terms of extent of tumor for better treatment planning, especially in patients who do not concentration radioactive I-131 (2) the relationship of tumor involvement to vital structures, especially in the neck and central nervous system